{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":192275,"duration_api_ms":186741,"num_turns":60,"result":"The fix is complete. Here's a summary of the changes made:\n\n## Summary\n\nFixed the bug where `dvc checkout/remove` were not able to handle broken symlinks.\n\n### Root Cause\n`os.path.exists()` follows symlinks to check if the target exists, returning `False` for broken symlinks. `os.path.lexists()` checks if the symlink entry itself exists, regardless of the target.\n\n### Changes Made\n\n**`dvc/utils/__init__.py`:**\n1. Changed `os.path.exists(path)` to `os.path.lexists(path)` in the `remove()` function to properly detect broken symlinks.\n2. Added a special case to handle symlinks by unlinking them directly (symlinks don't need chmod).\n3. Changed `os.stat(p)` to `os.lstat(p)` in the `_chmod` helper to avoid following symlinks.\n\n**`dvc/remote/local.py`:**\n1. Changed three occurrences of `os.path.exists()` to `os.path.lexists()` in the `do_checkout()` method to properly detect broken symlinks during checkout operations.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"49f33ec7-4c95-4a89-b19f-5f97a125f368","total_cost_usd":3.0130575,"usage":{"input_tokens":922408,"cache_creation_input_tokens":454,"cache_read_input_tokens":224170,"output_tokens":11792,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"cache_deleted_input_tokens":0,"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"MiniMax-M2.5-highspeed":{"inputTokens":922408,"outputTokens":11792,"cacheReadInputTokens":224170,"cacheCreationInputTokens":454,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":3.0130575,"contextWindow":196000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"069714a3-5879-4a7f-8a32-9a738027da2b"}
